repos/dali-ui/wiki/ScrollView.md:421:> `ScrollStartedSignal` fires only once per scroll session. `ScrollFinishedSignal` fires when all motion (including the fling animation) has stopped.
repos/dali-ui/wiki/ScrollView.md:503:- **`IsScrolling()` covers both drag and fling.** The flag is set to `true` at `ScrollStartedSignal` and cleared at `ScrollFinishedSignal`, so it remains `true` during the entire fling animation phase after the user lifts their finger.
repos/dali-ui/wiki/ScrollView.md:505:- **`DragFinishedSignal` precedes `ScrollFinishedSignal`.** After the user releases the screen, `DragFinishedSignal` fires first. If a fling animation follows, `ScrollFinishedSignal` fires only after the animation completes.
